# Anti-Overengineering

V1 exists for workflow validation and learning — not scaling, enterprise readiness, or future-proofing.

## MUST

- Choose the simpler option when uncertain.
- Build only what V1 specs and `docs/phase-b-architecture-map.md` require.
- Prefer small, understandable systems over clever abstractions.
- Use acceptable V1 shortcuts (mocks, fixtures, manual flows) when the core workflow stays valid.

## MUST NOT

- Add features because they seem useful, interesting, or "might be needed later."
- Introduce extra tables, services, libraries, or patterns not required by specs.
- Future-proof V1 for scale, multi-series, enterprise, analytics, or payments.
- Add configuration, flexibility, or customization beyond the four required inputs + optional fields.
- Optimize for performance or architecture elegance before the core workflow works.

## Feature test

If it does not reduce time-to-first-story or validate the core workflow — exclude it.
